                            <h3>Guidance on Principles for the Effective Management of Climate-Related Financial Risks</h3>
                        </adgm-text>

                            <adgm-text variant="textXS" italic="">

                                        Published 12 Nov 2023
                                    
, 
                                        Updated 12 Nov 2023
                                                                </adgm-text>
                    </adgm-flex>

                    <adgm-flex gap="rBodyXS">
                            <adgm-text variant="textS">
                                <p><p><span>The Financial Services Regulatory Authority (FSRA) of Abu Dhabi Global Market (ADGM), together with other members of the UAE Sustainable Finance Working Group (SFWG), has issued the Guidance on Principles for the Effective Management of Climate-Related Financial Risks. The Principles constitute a declaration of common understanding among the SFWG members on the minimum standards that they expect to implement in their respective jurisdictions and in line with their legal frameworks in the area of climate risk management.</span></p></p>
                            </adgm-text>
                        

                            <adgm-text variant="textXS" italic="">
